description:
Are you a Java developer who is ready for a new challenge? With us, you will work on innovative solutions within the Social Domain of the municipalities. Together with a driven team, you will build scalable applications and you will be given the freedom to put your creativity into the code. We value your skills, offer room for growth and ensure a good balance between work and fun. Does this sound like your ideal challenge? Let us hear from you!
What are you going to do
• You analyze functional descriptions (stories) and advise the Product Owner on the approach to be followed;
• You ensure technical coordination with your team members and architects;
• You are actively involved in innovation of the applications within our domain and security and architecture frameworks.

Our client has been a trusted partner for Dutch municipalities for over 70 years, providing innovative software solutions that support local governments in areas such as finance, public services, and spatial planning.

As a leading supplier of software and service concepts, they are constantly seeking the latest IT advancements to improve government efficiency. Their Social Affairs business unit specializes in software that seamlessly integrates information across policy areas, delivering a comprehensive customer view to enhance service delivery and decision making.

With a team of approximately 375 professionals, they are committed to continuous improvement, collaboration, and driving innovation in the public sector.
Function criteria
• You have completed a higher professional education/university education;
• Minimum 5 years of experience as a developer in Java;
• Experience with Spring Boot and/or J2EE;
• Experience with Cloud/SaaS development;
• Mastery of both Afrikaans/Dutch and English, both spoken and written;
• You have experience with Agile working;
• You are strongly focused on achieving results and quality;
• You have excellent communication skills;
• You are Dedicated, Enterprising and Progressive (the core values of our company);
• You have a positive attitude and enjoy taking on challenges;
• You have a good command of the English language, both spoken and written.

Pré: You have experience with
• Frontend development (e.g. VueJS);
• Software Architecture and Design Patterns;
• OWASP, Threat modeling, Security by Design;
• Infrastructure as code, ARM, Bicep.
Job offer

Working from home is an important part of our working method, but many team members also meet weekly at our beautiful location in Den Bosch.

Relocation package with step-by-step assistance with your relocation processes and covered virtual sessions with our relocation experts.

Visa application and 30% tax ruling application done by Ir Olav’s Globetrotters on your behalf.

Great South African community waiting for you in the Netherlands.

26 days of vacation per year, plus you can buy an additional 10 days (pro rata, of course).

Market related salary.

Dutch Government authorized pension plan activated once you arrive in the Netherlands.

One on one Dutch lessons up until company requirement where your partner can join lessons for free.

Company laptop.

Unlimited access to OpenUp and GoodHabitz (our online learning platform).

Commitment for indefinite contract with our client.

Mentoring and coaching until you go over to the payroll of our client.

Great on and offline events to meet your fellow Globetrotters and learn about the Netherlands, hosted by Ir Olav's Globetrotters.

Pleasant working atmosphere, where you can be and stay yourself.
How to apply

Are you just as excited as us about this role? Great! Then you're sure to be a good match! Applying for a job with us is very easy. Send your CV and motivation, using the application button, or email us at recruitment@irolav.world.
